<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[192,1440,1871,1929]" lastBlockId="15.[192,1440,217,370]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="14" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,1871,1895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zeller" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[472,627,1872,1896]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Hellinsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paleaceus">
<emphasis box="[472,627,1872,1896]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">H. paleaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with white to light buff forewing ground color and a small drab or fuscous spot at cleft base (may be diffuse) (
<figureCitation box="[695,779,1904,1929]" captionStart="Figures 10–17" captionStartId="26.[192,285,1762,1784]" captionTargetBox="[244,1388,213,1728]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[244,1388,213,1728]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figures 10–17. Bahamas Pterophoridae pinned adults. 10) Dejongia californicus ♀, San Salvador Island, 26.vii.2015. 11) Exelastis pumilio ♂, Abaco, 2.xi.2014. 12) Exelastis montischristi ♀, Cat Island, 25.vi.2014. 13) Exelastis dowi ♂, Abaco, 30.x.2014. 14) Emmelina buscki ♀, Grand Bahama Island, 27.x.2014. 15) Oidaematophorus androsensis Matthews, new species, ♀, holotype, North Andros Island, 11.vi.2012. 16) Hellinsia paleaceus ♂, Abaco, 6.vi.2016. 17) Hellinsia chlorias ♂, Crooked Island, 20.ix.1988. Scale line below each name equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3673608" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3673608/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Hindwing pale drab. Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Zeller" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[1288,1440,1904,1928]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Hellinsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paleaceus">
<emphasis box="[1288,1440,1904,1928]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="13">H. paleaceus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by drab or fuscous scales marking terminus of forewing veins R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[951,960,233,247]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">4</subScript>
, R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[992,1001,232,246]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">5</subScript>
, M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1039,1048,233,247]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">3</subScript>
, Cu 
<subScript attach="right" box="[1096,1105,233,247]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">1</subScript>
, and Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1204,1213,233,247]" fontSize="6" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">2</subScript>
. Left valve of male genitalia enlarged and bearing long curved saccular process (figured in 
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews, D. L. &amp; J. Y. Miller &amp; M. J. Simon &amp; G. Goss" box="[1067,1330,249,274]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref20878" refString="Matthews, D. L., J. Y. Miller, M. J. Simon, and G. Goss. 2012. Observations of plume moths on North Andros Island, Bahamas, and notes on new records and species previously recorded from the Bahamas (Lepidoptera: Pterophoridae). Insecta Mundi 0236: 1 - 12." type="book chapter" year="2012">Matthews et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). Female genitalia distinguished from related species by characteristic shape and sclerotization of tergite VIII anterior margin and anterior apophyses (
<collectingCountry box="[707,823,313,337]" name="Bahamas" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Bahamas</collectingCountry>
specimen not available, Florida specimen figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews, D. L." box="[228,435,345,370]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref20633" refString="Matthews, D. L. 1989. The plume moths of Florida (Lepidoptera: Pterophoridae). MS Thesis, University of Florida; Gainesville. 347 p." type="book" year="1989">Matthews (1989)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tutt" authorityYear="1905" box="[477,589,345,369]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Hellinsia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[477,589,345,369]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Hellinsia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. B).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,393,482]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,362,393,417]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Life history.</emphasis>
Larvae are stem borers on 
<taxonomicName authority="(Nutt.) Raf." authorityName="Raf." baseAuthorityName="Nutt." box="[710,1141,393,418]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Croptilon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="divaricatum">
<emphasis box="[710,986,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Croptilon divaricatum</emphasis>
(Nutt.) Raf.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1154,1388,393,417]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Conyza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canadensis">
<emphasis box="[1154,1388,393,417]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Conyza canadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Cronquist, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lam.) Britton and Rusby" authorityName="Britton and Rusby" baseAuthorityName="Lam." box="[379,990,425,450]" class="Monothalamea" family="Lagynidae" genus="Heterotheca" kingdom="Chromista" order="Allogromiida" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="subaxillaris">
<emphasis box="[379,674,425,449]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Heterotheca subaxillaris</emphasis>
(Lam.) Britton and Rusby
</taxonomicName>
in Florida. 
<taxonomicName box="[1127,1357,425,449]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Conyza" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canadensis">
<emphasis box="[1127,1357,425,449]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Conyza canadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs throughout most of 
<collectingCountry box="[433,604,457,481]" name="Bahamas" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">The Bahamas</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Correll, D. S. &amp; H. B. Correll" box="[619,922,457,482]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" refId="ref20417" refString="Correll, D. S., and H. B. Correll. 1982. Flora of the Bahama Archipelago (Including the Turks and Caicos Islands). Gantner Verlag; Vaduz, Liechtenstein. 1692 p." type="book" year="1982">Correll and Correll 1982</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1441,505,594]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,371,505,529]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species has been collected sporadically across the 
<collectingCountry box="[1045,1103,506,530]" name="United States of America" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">USA</collectingCountry>
with most records from the southeastern states. In 
<collectingCountry box="[483,654,537,561]" name="Bahamas" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">The Bahamas</collectingCountry>
it is known from only one specimen collected on 
<collectingRegion box="[1253,1441,537,561]" country="Bahamas" name="Crooked Island and Long Cay" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Crooked Island</collectingRegion>
and was previously reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Matthews, D. L. &amp; J. Y. Miller &amp; M. J. Simon &amp; G. Goss" box="[583,861,569,594]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref20878" refString="Matthews, D. L., J. Y. Miller, M. J. Simon, and G. Goss. 2012. Observations of plume moths on North Andros Island, Bahamas, and notes on new records and species previously recorded from the Bahamas (Lepidoptera: Pterophoridae). Insecta Mundi 0236: 1 - 12." type="book chapter" year="2012">Matthews et al. (2012)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="14" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[192,1440,617,706]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,345,617,641]" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Comments.</emphasis>
No additional specimens have been collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[937,1110,617,641]" name="Bahamas" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">The Bahamas</collectingCountry>
. The 
<collectingRegion box="[1176,1363,617,641]" country="Bahamas" name="Crooked Island and Long Cay" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Crooked Island</collectingRegion>
specimen (
<figureCitation box="[261,346,649,674]" captionStart="Figures 10–17" captionStartId="26.[192,285,1762,1784]" captionTargetBox="[244,1388,213,1728]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[244,1388,213,1728]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Figures 10–17. Bahamas Pterophoridae pinned adults. 10) Dejongia californicus ♀, San Salvador Island, 26.vii.2015. 11) Exelastis pumilio ♂, Abaco, 2.xi.2014. 12) Exelastis montischristi ♀, Cat Island, 25.vi.2014. 13) Exelastis dowi ♂, Abaco, 30.x.2014. 14) Emmelina buscki ♀, Grand Bahama Island, 27.x.2014. 15) Oidaematophorus androsensis Matthews, new species, ♀, holotype, North Andros Island, 11.vi.2012. 16) Hellinsia paleaceus ♂, Abaco, 6.vi.2016. 17) Hellinsia chlorias ♂, Crooked Island, 20.ix.1988. Scale line below each name equals 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3673608" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3673608/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="14">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) has more scattered drab scales basad of the forewing cleft spot than is typical of Florida individuals but falls within the range of variation seen for the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
